channel.title: WinRAR - Access is Denied
channel.description:
I read the section rules before i posted this.
[b]Problem[/b]
Im following a guide to create my own RS server, and in the guide ill have to change stuff in Client.java and other files to make it mine. but while in WinRAR, and change something in Client.java (Opened with notepad) And i changed the names of the server to mine, and i exit and saved it in the notepad, and it asks me if i want to update it in the archive, and i get this.
Cannot Create C:\Documents and Settings\******\Local Settings\Temp\TestScape Source-1.rar Access is Denied.
My friend who is playing on his computer at my house has done exactly what im trying, but does not get this error. I have tried to look up this problem, tried 15-25 different answers, but none of them are explicit to this problem.

item.title: WinRAR - Access is Denied
item.dc:creator: @Umah Umah
item.description:
@Umah wrote:

[quote=“Generalizaac, post:7, topic:291419”]I got it fixed, but a new problem popped up, and before asking, i looked everywhere, but no where gives an explanation on how to fix it.

After i compile the server, as the guide says, i get this.

Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API.
Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details.
Press any button to continue . . .

If anyone can tell me how to deal with this step-by-step, will be appreciated.[/quote]
Lol, that means nothing’s wrong with it, no errors. It says that everytime you compile. Simply means you did it right.
